data.content:
The root cause is that ASP.NET Core 10 upgraded from **Microsoft.OpenApi v1.x → v2.x**, which targets OpenAPI 3.1 and has several breaking API changes. Here are the four issues and fixes:

---

**1. `OpenApiString` / `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` removed**
The entire `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace is gone. Examples are now `JsonNode`.

```csharp
// Before
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// After
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

---

**2. `Schema.Nullable` removed**
OpenAPI 3.1 expresses nullability via the `type` keyword. `OpenApiSchema.Type` is now a `JsonSchemaType` flags enum.

```csharp
// Before
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// After
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

---

**3. `OpenApiSecurityScheme.Reference` / `ReferenceType` removed**
Dedicated reference classes replace the generic `Reference` property pattern.

```csharp
// Before
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};

// After
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
```

---

**4. `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` key type changed**
It now expects `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference` as the key (follows naturally from fix #3 — no additional syntax change needed).

---

**Corrected code:**

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters?.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses ??= new Dictionary<string, OpenApiResponse>();
    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**Summary of namespace changes:**
| Removed | Replacement |
|---|---|
| `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | `System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| `OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, … | `JsonValue.Create(…)` |
| `OpenApiReference` + `ReferenceType` | `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`, `OpenApiSchemaReference`, etc. in `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References` |
| `Schema.Nullable` (bool) | `Schema.Type` flags with `JsonSchemaType.Null` |
